A HALLOWE'EN festival is to take place for the first time in Paisley. Festival to make spooky town debut A HALLOWE'EN festival is to take place for the first time in Paisley.It starts tomorrow at 6pm with a lantern-lit fancy dress parade from Paisley Museum to Abbey Close and will feature 200 children, drummers, illuminated giant birds and walkers with lightsThere will also be a fire garden of sculptures made from flames. 